#: ../source/notebooks/clv/sBG.ipynb:20004 e3298b13996945b3b4d3d6491012451d
msgid ""
"Fader, P. S., & Hardie, B. G. (2007). How to project customer retention. "
"Journal of Interactive Marketing, 21(1), 76-90. "
"https://journals.sagepub.com/doi/pdf/10.1002/dir.20074"
msgstr ""

#: ../source/notebooks/clv/sBG.ipynb:20006 7023446dfb4047f9a206151a14cb3449
msgid ""
"The authors describe the Shifted Beta Geometric (sBG) model for customer "
"behavior in a discrete contractual setting. It assumes that:"
msgstr ""

#: ../source/notebooks/clv/sBG.ipynb:20007 236d042a05f443cd9aa30dd02cf77b85
msgid ""
"At the end of each period, a customer has a probability `theta` of "
"renewing the contract and `1-theta` of cancelling"
msgstr ""

#: ../source/notebooks/clv/sBG.ipynb:20009 79427e96f8e7460d90099acada61e8bf
msgid "The probability `theta` does not change over time for a given customer"
msgstr ""

#: ../source/notebooks/clv/sBG.ipynb:20010 95f584c5a58f4162b29d73f20f1f4a70
msgid ""
"The probability `theta` varies across customers according to a Beta prior"
" distribution with hyperparameters `alpha` and `beta`."
msgstr ""

#: ../source/notebooks/clv/sBG.ipynb:50002 05c2de0701fc4265a7709b4845378450
msgid "Recreating the dataset"
msgstr ""

#: ../source/notebooks/clv/sBG.ipynb:60002 a923ef794fd5460aaff14ceb5c44e541
msgid ""
"The dataset contains the percentage of customers still enrolled in the "
"service after each time period. There are two distinct groups of users: "
"regular and high-end, believed to have different attrition rates. Each "
"group had 1000 customers at the start."
msgstr ""

#: ../source/notebooks/clv/sBG.ipynb:60004 d922a417c9e84a45aaa47f4683ccfc8a
msgid ""
"As in the original paper, we will fit the data from the first 7 time "
"periods only, and use the following periods for validation."
msgstr ""

#: ../source/notebooks/clv/sBG.ipynb:80002 3ac63a36fbf541b8997056ce96084dbb
msgid ""
"The implemented pymc-marketing model fits each individual `theta`,  in "
"contrast to the paper approach where the inidividual parameters are "
"marginalized out."
msgstr ""

#: ../source/notebooks/clv/sBG.ipynb:80005 012fabccabd24f6e926b8929270a5589
msgid ""
"For our analysis we wil have to create a synthetic dataset with "
"individual data, following the aggregate group trends."
msgstr ""

#: ../source/notebooks/clv/sBG.ipynb:110002 8a499d0457cc40f18196a0884b421f1f
msgid ""
"Customers which haven't churned have `t_churn == T == 8`.  The model will"
" handle these differently, as their lifetimes are "
"[censored](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Censoring_(statistics))."
msgstr ""

#: ../source/notebooks/clv/sBG.ipynb:120002 82d6ad26f23147289aec59a3f6b83157
msgid "Fitting the sBG models for high end and regular users"
msgstr ""

